{{Infobox church | name = Church of the Holy Cross | fullname = Crkva Svetog Križa | location = {{Flagicon|Croatia}} [[Nin, Croatia|Nin]], [[Croatia]] | color = | image = Heilig_Kreuz_Kirche_in_Nin,_Kroatien_2.jpg | imagesize = 250px | caption = | denomination = [[Roman Catholic]] | architect = | style = [[Pre-Romanesque]] | completed date = 9th century | country = | website = }} '''Church of the Holy Cross''' ({{lang-hr|Crkva svetog Križa}}) is a Croatian [[Pre-Romanesque]] [[Catholic]] [[Church (building)|church]] originating from the 9th century in [[Nin, Croatia|Nin]].<ref name="zadarskanadbiskupija">http://www.zadarskanadbiskupija.hr/?p=4009</ref>
According to a theory from an art [[historian]] Mladen Pejaković,<ref name=sun/> the design has an intentionally unbalanced [[ellipse|elliptical]] form designated to "follow" the position of the [[Sun]], retaining the functionality of a [[calendar]] and [[sundial]].<ref name=sun/> In its beginning, in the time of the [[Littoral Croatian Duchy|Croatian principality]], it was used as a royal [[chapel]] of the [[duke]]'s [[courtyard]] nearby.<ref name=sun>{{cite journal|url=http://www.casopis-gradjevinar.hr/dokumenti/200907/6.pdf |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091229173122/http://www.casopis-gradjevinar.hr/dokumenti/200907/6.pdf|title=Crkve u sjeverozapadnom dijelu zadarskoga zaleđa|journal=Građevinar|issue=61|year=2009|archivedate=December 29, 2009|language=hr}}</ref>
The church is that of a central type, it features the [[Croatian interlace]] (or simply "troplet") and a carved name of the Croatian ''župan'' "Godečaj".<ref name=sun/><ref>{{hr icon}} [https://web.archive.org/web/20070509063433/http://www.nin.hr/hr/kulturne_znamenitosti.html Nin.hr - kulturne znamenitosti] ''/'' [https://archive.is/20130217172608/http://kulturniturizam.croatia.hr/Destinations/DestinationDocument.aspx?idLanguage=1&idDestination=192&idCategory=1061&idDocument=2860 Kulturni turizam - croatia.hr - Nin: Crkva sv. Križa - najmanja katedrala na svijetu]</ref>
The church is known under the moniker of "the smallest [[cathedral]] in the world",<ref name="zadarskanadbiskupija"/><ref>{{hr icon}} [https://web.archive.org/web/20080804072615/http://www.izaberi.hr/index.php?lang=hr&op=sd&tip=mje&id=0000024 Izaberi.hr - Nin]</ref><ref>{{hr icon}} [http://www.arbela.hr/hr-nin.html http://www.arbela.hr/hr-nin.html ]</ref> but it does not actually contain the seat of a [[bishop of Nin]] today.
