{{Infobox musical artist |name = The Oppressed |image = |caption = |background = group_or_band |origin = [[Cardiff]], [[Wales]] |genre = [[Oi!]], [[punk rock|punk]] |years_active = 1981-1984, 1994-1996, 1998-2006, 2009-2016. |associated_acts = |label = Oppressed Records, Step-1 Music, Oi! Records, Dojo, Knockout, [[Insurgence Records]], [[Captain Oi! Records]] |past_members = }}
'''The Oppressed''' is a [[Wales|Welsh]] [[Oi!]] band that formed in 1981 in [[Cardiff]], [[Wales]], [[UK]]. Most of the musicians in the band's various lineups have been [[skinhead]]s. Throughout the band's career, the members (especially vocalist Roddy Moreno) openly expressed opposition to [[racism]] and [[fascism]]<ref>http://www.allmusic.com/artist/the-oppressed-mn0000476048/biography</ref> — in their lyrics,<ref>http://www.allmusic.com/album/music-for-hooligans-mw0000616387</ref> interviews, on-stage comments and other actions. In 1989, Moreno visited [[New York City]] and met a few members of [[Skinheads Against Racial Prejudice]] (SHARP). On his return to the [[United Kingdom]], he started promoting SHARP ideals to British skinheads.<ref>[http://www.theoppressed.co.uk/home.html The Oppressed; Official Website<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref><ref>[http://www.bbc.co.uk/wales/music/sites/oppressed/ BBC - Wales - The Oppressed<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> The band has also had ties to other anti-racist groups, such as [[Anti-Fascist Action]]. Moreno is a [[Cardiff City F.C.]] supporter, and some of the band's songs express that support.
The band has split and re-formed several times, the first occasion in 1984 after which Moreno focused on his record labels, Oi! Records and Ska Records for the remainder of the decade.<ref>http://www.discogs.com/label/145573-Oi!-Records</ref><ref>http://www.insurgence.net/component/content/article/144</ref> Their most recent split was in 2006, but they re-formed in 2009, and continue performing today.
The Oppressed 2013 line up featured, alongside Roddy Moreno on vocals and guitar, Paul Cobley on bass and Tony Kizmus on drums.
